args: If they're aiming to fire their new weapon\nat the town, then the easiest spot for that\nwould be just ahead.

It will launch a great cylinder into the sky,
which will detonate, raining innumerable
bullets down on the hapless people below.
Their screams will rise in a chorus of pain!
The genius Gennai is truly without peer!\nSuch a frightful weapon he has created.\nNow, set it off.
Igniting now! Time until Hellfyre launch:\nsixty seconds! Fifty-nine, fifty-eight...
That giant cylinder pointed at the sky is\nthe Mukuroshu's new weapon!
Tch! Looks like they're done getting it\nready to launch. But we're still pretty far!
There's a talisman attached to the end of\nthe cylinder. It's probably a jufu set in\norder to regulate the time of the explosion.
I'll shoot it. Doing that ought to cause it\nto detonate before it leaves the ground.
Mukuroshu fiends!\nThey're trying to stop us!
We'll handle this, Saiga.\nYou take care of the weapon!
You talked a mean game about all this,\nso you better make damn sure you stop it!
I can aim right at the jufu from here.\nSteady, Saiga. Ready, aim...
Ngh... The wind is too strong. The shot's\ntrajectory will be off if I fire now!
If you shoot the jufu, it'll cause an\nexplosion, and all the bullets in the\ncylinder will come flying here.
You won't escape unscathed from a rain of\nbullets. You might save the people of the\ntown, but you'll pay with your life. Still...

You think I'll let you die a martyr?
Back down. Don't atone. Save no one.
Just die the same villainous dog you've
always been.
You are an illusion borne of my regret and\nmy fear. Your words are the pain in my\nheart made manifest.

I was...afraid of Yachiyo's forgiveness.
I wondered if it was all right for me to
live a carefree life, having taken so many
others for my own selfish desires.

The dead will not return. There is no worth
in living for myself. But to use that as an
excuse to choose an ugly death is nothing
but flagrant self-indulgence.
And that would mean nothing had changed\nfrom the time when I had selfishly fallen\nto depravity. Thus, I must continue to fight.
Not to live, and not to die.\nBut to stand upright once more.
What the—was that a caster shot?!
Boss! The jufu on the Hellfyre has been\nhit! At this rate, it will...!
Is this a dream...? No.\nThis is my life flashing before my eyes.
I haven't yet atoned enough, but it seems\nI may have met a premature end...
I am not long for this world. Permit me\nto make a final request of you, Saiga.
Momoyo and I were watching the flowers\nas their falling petals danced in the wind.\nAs we did, she asked something of me.
Saiga. Watch over Yachiyo in my place.
She has a competitive spirit, but\nshe's a deeply lonely girl at heart.
In my sorrow over losing her,\nI forgot her final request.
I am sorry, Momoyo.\nBut I know Yachiyo will be fine.
She has become a handsome warrior.\nI need not save her, for she is the one\nwho saved me.
I know she will thrive, even if I pass on.
And you swore to her, didn't you? That\nyou would live a life free from shame?
?! Are these not words from my memory?\nIs she truly speaking to me?
Yachiyo is strong, but still, there will\nbe times when she loses her way.
And you, upright as you are,\nwill be there to support her.
So I want you to live on, ever facing\nforward, until the end. For my beloved\nYachiyo.
And...for me, the woman who wishes\nyou nothing but happiness.
I love you, Saiga.\nI will be with you, always and forever.
Addis... Is this an inn in Quinbell?
After the failed launch of the new weapon,\nwe found you collapsed, and brought you\nhere.
I must have been teetering on the brink\nof death. What of the new weapon?\nAnd the Mukuroshu?
Smashed to bits. And we took down the\nworkshop in the Zarroch Mine.
Unfortunately, we lost track of the one who\nmade the weapon, Gennai, in the chaos.\nWe don't know where he is.
If we don't capture him, he could well\nmake another of his vile creations.
Whoop. There's the telltale pitter-patter\nof footsteps.
Addis! Gozu Tenno! Why didn't you tell\nme the second he woke up?!
Yeah, I heard you went down, hard!\nGah, you are such an idiot!
Even if you were trying to foil a Mukuroshu\nplot, you went too far. WAY too far.
You're gonna have hell to pay if you try\nto go and die on me again. Honestly...!
I'm sorry, Yachiyo. But I will not worry\nyou again.
I will continue living, harrowed by regret\nand fear, in order to do what I must do.
I swore as much to you, and I intend\nto follow through. For your sake...\nand Momoyo's.
